                  <origin>
                     <origPlace>
                        <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0171KY">Koholo Yoḥannǝs Dabra Betel / KY</placeName>
                     </origPlace>
                     <origDate notBefore="1780" notAfter="1820">Parchment guards in quire I
                        originate from a different, older Ms. (15th cent.?).</origDate>
                  </origin>
                  <provenance>The names of Gabra Ṣādǝq (<locus target="#4r">4r</locus>, 52r, 82r) and Walda Mikāʾel, Kǝfla Giwärgis, Walatta Madḫǝn,
                     Sǝlṭanä Krǝstos (<locus target="#52r">52r</locus>, 132r) are written in a
                     secondary hand. According to Additio 3, Gabra Ṣādǝq is the father of fitawrari
                     Tawalda Madḫǝn. The Ms. was apparently initially owned by
                     Sǝlṭanä Krǝstos (Additio 6). Afterwards it passed to Qʷǝrbāna Dǝngǝl and his
                     wife Säbänä Giyorgis (Additio 5). The last recorded owner was fitawrari Tawalda
                     Madḫǝn (Waldu), his wife was wayzaro Nǝrʾaya
                     (Additiones 1-3).</provenance>
